      "writtenOn": "2016-03-23T22:07:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s a safety measure. Since \"success\" isn\u0027t boolean, it might have any value if used incorrectly in the preceding code. Any value other that GL_TRUE (even non-zero one) indicates that there was some sort of problem. Also, theoretically, the spec does not guarantee that GL_FALSE is 0 (afaik) so it\u0027s always better to check those explicitly. I even changed the (!success) above to an explicit comparison.",
